#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:192
#, no-c-format
msgid "Basic usage"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:194
#, no-c-format
msgid "The System V init system uses several commands to handle services&mdash;the init scripts, <command>insserv</command> , <command>telinit</command> and others. &systemd; makes it easier to manage services, since there is only one command to memorize for the majority of service-handling tasks: <command>systemctl</command> . It uses the <quote>command plus subcommand</quote> notation like <command>git</command> or <command>zypper</command> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:199
#, no-c-format
msgid "systemctl <replaceable>GENERAL OPTIONS</replaceable> <replaceable>SUBCOMMAND</replaceable> <replaceable>SUBCOMMAND OPTIONS</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:201
#, no-c-format
msgid "See <command>man 1 systemctl</command> for a complete manual."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:206
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminal output and Bash completion"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:207
#, no-c-format
msgid "If the output goes to a terminal (and not to a pipe or a file, for example), &systemd; commands send long output to a pager by default. Use the <option>--no-pager</option> option to turn off paging mode."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:211
#, no-c-format
msgid "&systemd; also supports bash-completion, allowing you to enter the first letters of a subcommand and then press <keycap function=\"tab\"/> . This feature is only available in the <systemitem>bash</systemitem> shell and requires the installation of the package <systemitem class=\"resource\">bash-completion</systemitem> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Managing services in a running system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:219
#, no-c-format
msgid "Subcommands for managing services are the same as for managing a service with System V init ( <command>start</command> , <command>stop</command> , ...). The general syntax for service management commands is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: systemd.xml:225
#, no-c-format
msgid "&systemd;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: listitem
#: systemd.xml:226
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>systemctl reload|restart|start|status|stop|<replaceable>...</replaceable> <replaceable>MY_SERVICE(S)</replaceable></screen>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: systemd.xml:231
#, no-c-format
msgid "System V init"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: listitem
#: systemd.xml:232
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>rc<replaceable>MY_SERVICE(S)</replaceable> reload|restart|start|status|stop|<replaceable>...</replaceable></screen>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "&systemd; allows you to manage several services in one go. Instead of executing init scripts one after the other as with System V init, execute a command like the following:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:241
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl start <replaceable>MY_1ST_SERVICE</replaceable> <replaceable>MY_2ND_SERVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:242
#, no-c-format
msgid "To list all services available on the system:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl list-unit-files --type=service"
msgstr ""

