#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:429
#, no-c-format
msgid "Permanently enabling/disabling services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:430
#, no-c-format
msgid "The service management commands mentioned in the previous section let you manipulate services for the current session. &systemd; also lets you permanently enable or disable services, so they are automatically started when requested or are always unavailable. You can either do this by using &yast;, or on the command line."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:435
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enabling/disabling services on the command line"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:436
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following table lists enabling and disabling commands for &systemd; and System V init:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:440
#, no-c-format
msgid "Service start"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:441
#, no-c-format
msgid "When enabling a service on the command line, it is not started automatically. It is scheduled to be started with the next system start-up or runlevel/target change. To immediately start a service after having enabled it, explicitly run <command>systemctl start <replaceable>MY_SERVICE</replaceable></command> or <command>rc <replaceable>MY_SERVICE</replaceable> start</command> ."
msgstr ""

