#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:1717
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminating services (sending signals)"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1718
#, no-c-format
msgid "As explained in <xref linkend=\"sec-boot-systemd-advanced-cgroups\"/> , it is not always possible to assign a process to its parent service process in a System V init system. This makes it difficult to terminate a service and all of its children. Child processes that have not been terminated will remain as zombie processes."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1723
#, no-c-format
msgid "&systemd;'s concept of confining each service into a cgroup makes it possible to clearly identify all child processes of a service and therefore allows you to send a signal to each of these processes. Use <command>systemctl kill</command> to send signals to services. For a list of available signals refer to <command>man 7 signals</command> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: systemd.xml:1730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sending <systemitem>SIGTERM</systemitem> to a service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1732
#, no-c-format
msgid "<systemitem>SIGTERM</systemitem> is the default signal that is sent."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:1735
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl kill <replaceable>MY_SERVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: term
#: systemd.xml:1739
