#. Tag: term
#: systemd.xml:1748
#, no-c-format
msgid "Selecting processes"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1750
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default the <command>kill</command> command sends the signal to <option>all</option> processes of the specified cgroup. You can restrict it to the <option>control</option> or the <option>main</option> process. The latter is for example useful to force a service to reload its configuration by sending <systemitem>SIGHUP</systemitem> :"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: systemd.xml:1755
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.sudo;systemctl kill -s SIGHUP --kill-who=main <replaceable>MY_SERVICE</replaceable>"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:1762
#, no-c-format
msgid "Important notes on the D-Bus service"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1763
#, no-c-format
msgid "The D-Bus service is the message bus for communication between &systemd; clients and the systemd manager that is running as pid 1. Even though <systemitem class=\"daemon\">dbus</systemitem> is a stand-alone daemon, it is an integral part of the init infrastructure."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1767
#, no-c-format
msgid "Terminating <systemitem class=\"daemon\">dbus</systemitem> or restarting it in the running system is similar to an attempt to terminate or restart pid 1. It will break &systemd; client/server communication and make most &systemd; functions unusable."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1771
#, no-c-format
msgid "Therefore, terminating or restarting <systemitem class=\"daemon\">dbus</systemitem> is neither recommended nor supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1775
#, no-c-format
msgid "Updating the <systemitem>dbus</systemitem> or <systemitem>dbus</systemitem> -related packages requires a reboot. When in doubt whether a reboot is necessary, run the <command>sudo zypper ps -s</command> . If <literal>dbus</literal> appears among the listed services, you need to reboot the system."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1780
#, no-c-format
msgid "Keep in mind that <systemitem>dbus</systemitem> is updated even when automatic updates are configured to skip the packages that require reboot."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: systemd.xml:1788
#, no-c-format
msgid "Debugging services"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: systemd.xml:1789
#, no-c-format
msgid "By default, &systemd; is not overly verbose. If a service was started successfully, no output will be produced. In case of a failure, a short error message will be displayed. However, <command>systemctl status</command> provides means to debug start-up and operation of a service."
